<i>not to alienate her alibi.</i>

127
00:05:07,417 --> 00:05:10,083
This toast has hook holes...

128
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:13,417
...again! I told you to get rid
of that thing; it's hideous.

129
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:15,875
Plus, what's gonna happen
when they swear you in?

130
00:05:15,917 --> 00:05:17,792
You're gonna
rip the Bible in half.

131
00:05:17,834 --> 00:05:19,166
The jury will love that.

132
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:22,542
You're getting pretty snippy

133
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,083
to your key witness, aren't you?

134
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,750
What do you want?

135
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:29,208
Maybe you could hook me up
with a little stimmy.

136
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:33,500
Lil' stimmy.

137
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:34,583
Are you trying to do this?

138
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,375
Yes!

139
00:05:36,417 --> 00:05:38,208
And I want stimmy
to get a hook that'll do that.

140
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,041
<i>When no such hook</i>
<i>was available,</i>

141
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:43,834
<i>Lucille found other means</i>
<i>to mollify her alibi--</i>

142
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:47,000
<i>both of which were unveiled</i>
<i>at a family meeting.</i>

143
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:49,458
...you're the key witness
in your mother's trial.

144
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,125
Wait, I thought
I was the key witness.

145
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:52,750
-You're the star witness.
-Oh.

146
00:05:52,792 --> 00:05:55,583
Because it was your life
I was going after to save.

147
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,083
He fell off the boat.

148
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:59,083
-He'll tell you in my own words.
-(groans)

149
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,625
(mumbles):
Homosexuals kidnapped...

150
00:06:00,667 --> 00:06:03,083
Up-up-up.

151
00:06:03,125 --> 00:06:05,083
(loudly):
Homosexuals kidnapped the boat

152
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:07,000
