and she went back.

156
00:06:12,709 --> 00:06:14,667
Oh, and a fish swam by my ankle.

157
00:06:14,709 --> 00:06:16,208
(gasps)
That really happened.

158
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,542
Should I keep that?

159
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:18,875
-Make it an eel.
-Okay.

160
00:06:18,917 --> 00:06:20,792
-It's gonna be an eel!
-Better.

161
00:06:20,834 --> 00:06:23,917
<i>But alone with Buster,</i>
<i>the tension grew worse,</i>

162
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:27,709
<i>and things came to a head</i>
<i>the night before the trial.</i>

163
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,166
Buster, I'm going to exhale!

164
00:06:29,208 --> 00:06:30,959
No, please!

165
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,750
I've had, like, seven
in the past half hour.

166
00:06:33,792 --> 00:06:36,500
You're not the one
staring five years in the face.

167
00:06:36,542 --> 00:06:39,291
Well, right now, I'm staring at
a hundred years in the face!

168
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,041
(whispers):
How dare you.

169
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:44,542
Would you mind?

170
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:46,709
Be careful, defendant.

171
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:49,667
Remember who you're talking to.

172
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:51,917
It sure would be a shame
if something happened

173
